Created by FontForge 20140411 at Fri Jul 11 03:30:42 2014 By Ivan Kuzmin Important note! This charset isn't the true font, but only used to deploy few vector symbols as selectable. Letters was captured from the great DIN PT font. Copyright information from original font is given below.
DIN PT is a new font family of sans serif typefaces designed in ParaType on the base of well known German font developed in Deutsches Institut fur Normung e.V. (German Institute for Standardization) that was published in 1936 and registered as DIN 1451. The font has remembering geometric design and convey strong feeling of German "ordnung". Due to it naive rude shapes DIN font becomes very popular in the last years and begets enormous modern variations. ParaType version of DIN was developed by Dmitry Kirsanov and released in 2012.
